snippet.textDisplay: Most of what cows eat is indigestible to humans and many cow pastures are on non-arable land. A lot of the stuff about how badly cattle are treated is made up or badly exaggerated. And 3% of the world's greenhouse gas emissions (which would be produced by local megafauna anyway) is nothing compared to the ~100 companies that produce over 70% of the world's greenhouse gas emissions. Not to mention that the soy, almonds, oats, rice, etc. Are tended by underpaid, overworked, mistreated workers and have to be transported, sometimes hundreds of miles away from where they were grown. If you really want to make a difference wrt the environment, get into activism and demand that large companies be held responsible for the damage they cause. You can eat whatever you like, but don't spread misinformation because you think being vegan is morally superior to eating meat and dairy.
